{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77444368-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s410b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"410b"},"text":"§ 410b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Administration, protection, and development","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The administration, protection, and development of the aforesaid park shall be exercised under the direction of the Secretary of the Interior by the National Park Service, subject to the provisions of the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1916-08-25"},"text":"August 25, 1916","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/535"},"text":"39 Stat. 535","children":[],"tail":"), entitled “An Act to establish a National Park Service, and for other purposes”,"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002089"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002089"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" as amended: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That the provisions of the Federal Power Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 791a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] shall not apply to this park: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided further","children":[],"tail":", That nothing in sections 410 to 410c of this title shall be construed to lessen any existing rights of the Seminole Indians which are not in conflict with the purposes for which the Everglades National Park is created."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77444369-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-05-30/ch371/s3"},"text":"May 30, 1934, ch. 371, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/816"},"text":"48 Stat. 816","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1937-08-21/ch732"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1937, ch. 732","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/50/742"},"text":"50 Stat. 742","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7744436a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7744436b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7744436c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1916-08-25"},"text":"August 25, 1916","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/535"},"text":"39 Stat. 535","children":[],"tail":"), entitled “An Act to establish a National Park Service, and for other purposes”, referred to in text, is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1916-08-25/ch408"},"text":"act Aug. 25, 1916, ch. 408","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/39/535"},"text":"39 Stat. 535","children":[],"tail":", known as the National Park Service Organic Act, which enacted sections 1, 2, 3, and 4 of this title and provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t54/s100101"},"text":"section 100101 of Title 54","children":[],"tail":", National Park Service and Related Programs. Sections 1 to 4 of the Act were repealed and restated as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s1865/a"},"text":"section 1865(a) of Title 18","children":[],"tail":", Crimes and Criminal Procedure, and section 100101(a), chapter 1003, and sections 100751(a), 100752, 100753, and 102101 of Title 54 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3, 4(a)(1), 7, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3094"},"text":"128 Stat. 3094","children":[],"tail":", 3260, 3272. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables. For disposition of former sections of this title, see Disposition Table preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t54/s100101"},"text":"section 100101 of Title 54","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Power Act, referred to in text, was in the original the “Act approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1920","children":[],"tail":", known as the Federal Water Power Act,” and was redesignated as the Federal Power Act by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":". The Federal Power Act is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-10/ch285"},"text":"act June 10, 1920, ch. 285","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/1063"},"text":"41 Stat. 1063","children":[],"tail":", and is classified generally to chapter 12 (§ 791a et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id7744436d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1937—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1937-08-21"},"text":"Aug. 21, 1937","children":[],"tail":", struck out proviso which prohibited expenditure of public moneys by the United States on the park within a period of five years."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"id7744436e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id7744436f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions of other officers, employees, and agencies of Department of the Interior, with certain exceptions, to Secretary of the Interior, with power to delegate, see Reorg. Plan No. 3 of 1950, §§ 1, 2, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3174, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1262"},"text":"64 Stat. 1262","children":[],"tail":", set out in the Appendix to Title 5, Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
